Presidential elections were held in Azerbaijan on 3 October 1993. The result was a victory for incumbent president Heydar Aliyev of the New Azerbaijan Party, who won with nearly 99% of the vote. Election monitors characterized the elections as neither free nor fair.
Voter turnout was reported to be 98%.
